Leonard J. Leblanc  Independent Director, AXT, Inc.AgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 1 Board Members in 1 different organizations across 3 different industries.See Board Relationships76$122,543
Background

		Mr. Leonard J. LeBlanc, also known as Len, has been an Acting Chief Financial Officer and Vice President of Corporate Development of eBest Inc., since February 2001. Mr. LeBlanc served as an Executive Vice President and Chief Financial Officer of Vantive Corporation, a customer relationship management software and solution company, from August 1998 to January 2000 and served as its Secretary. He served as an Executive Vice President of Finance and Administration and ... Chief Financial Officer at Infoseek Corporation from March 1996 to July 1997. Mr. LeBlanc served as Senior Vice President of Finance and Administration and Chief Financial Officer of GTECH Corporation from September 1993 to December 1994. He served as an Executive Vice President of Finance and Administration and Chief Financial Officer of Cadence Design Systems, Inc. from May 1987 to December 1992. He served as the Chairman of Oplink Communications Inc., from February 17, 2006 to November 2009 and served as its Director from July 2000 to November 2009. He has been on the Board of Directors of eBest, Inc. since August 2000. He has been an Independent Director of AXT Inc. since April 21, 2003. He served as Director of Optical Communication Products Inc. since June 20, 2007. Mr. LeBlanc received his B.S. and M.S. from College of Holy Cross and his Masters Degree in Finance from George Washington University.Read Full Background




